"title": "5701: heir",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5701",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Property and power in biblical times normally descended from father to son. Jesus Christ is therefore called God's heir, and believers are said to inherit in him.</p>\n<h2>The heir in ancient Israel</h2>\n<h3>The heir of property</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:3-Gen15:4\">GEN 15:3–15:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:22\">PRO 13:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:14\">PRO 19:14</a></p>\n<h3>The heir of power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:12\">1KI 2:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:28\">1CH 29:28</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:43\">1KI 11:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:31\">1KI 14:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:3\">1KI 15:3</a></p>\n<h3>Lack of an heir regarded as a very serious matter</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:5-Deut25:6\">DEU 25:5–25:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:17\">JDG 21:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:4-2Sam14:7\">2SA 14:4–14:7</a> <em>The woman of Tekoa was interceding indirectly for Absalom, David's heir, who had been banished.</em></p>\n<h3>Daughters and other relatives could be heirs if there were no sons</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:1-Num27:11\">NUM 27:1–27:11</a></p>\n<h3>Property could be inherited before death</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:11-Luke15:12\">LUK 15:11–15:12</a> <em>The prodigal son's request of inheritance before death could perhaps be regarded as an insult, but graciously the father complied out of love.</em></p>\n<h3>An heir must not give up his inheritance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:16\">HEB 12:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:29-Gen25:34\">GEN 25:29–25:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:6-Num36:7\">NUM 36:6–36:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:3\">1KI 21:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:1\">JER 49:1</a></p>\n<h3>The firstborn son was heir to a double share</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:17\">DEU 21:17</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the heir of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:2\">HEB 1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18\">MAT 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:12\">LUK 19:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:35\">JHN 3:35</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is heir as the Father's firstborn</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:6\">HEB 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Envy of Jesus Christ as heir</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:37-Matt21:39\">MAT 21:37–21:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:6-Mark12:8\">MRK 12:6–12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:13-Luke20:15\">LUK 20:13–20:15</a></p>\n<h2>God's people as heirs</h2>\n<h3>God himself as his people's inheritance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:7\">JOS 18:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:26\">PSA 73:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:57\">PSA 119:57</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps142:5\">PSA 142:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:19\">JER 51:19</a></p>\n<h3>Israel as heirs to land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:13\">EXO 32:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:44\">PSA 105:44</a></p>\n<h3>Noah, heir of righteousness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:7\">HEB 11:7</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham, heir of promise</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:4-Gen17:8\">GEN 17:4–17:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:54-Luke1:55\">LUK 1:54–1:55</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8-Heb11:9\">HEB 11:8–11:9</a></p>\n<h3>David, heir of a kingdom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:8-2Sam7:16\">2SA 7:8–7:16</a></p>\n<h3>Israel, heirs of the prophets</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:25\">ACT 3:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:2\">ROM 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>All believers are heirs by faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:13-Rom4:17\">ROM 4:13–4:17</a></p>\n<h3>Heirs under the covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:17\">HEB 6:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a></p>\n<h3>Heirs through God's grace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:18\">GAL 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:12\">COL 1:12</a></p>\n<h3>Co-heirs with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17\">ROM 8:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The privileges of God's heirs</h2>\n<h3>Believers are heirs to the full rights of sons</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:1-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:1–4:7</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are heirs as the firstborn</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:23\">HEB 12:23</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are heirs of salvation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:14\">HEB 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are heirs of eternal life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:7\">TIT 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:3-1Pet1:4\">1PE 1:3–1:4</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are heirs of the earth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:5\">MAT 5:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:11\">PSA 37:11</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are heirs of the kingdom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:34\">MAT 25:34</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are heirs of all things</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:21-1Cor3:22\">1CO 3:21–3:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:10\">2CO 6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:7\">REV 21:7</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are heirs of life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:7\">1PE 3:7</a></p>\n<h3>Believers as heirs share Jesus Christ's throne</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:29-Luke22:30\">LUK 22:29–22:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:21\">REV 3:21</a></p>\n<h2>God's inheritance is his people</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:9\">DEU 32:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:12\">ZEC 2:12</a></p>",
